WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:22.360 align:middle line:90%


00:00:22.360 --> 00:00:27.620 align:middle line:84%
>> I felt this connection
with everything,

00:00:27.620 --> 00:00:28.675 align:middle line:90%
especially with nature.

00:00:28.675 --> 00:00:31.340 align:middle line:90%


00:00:31.340 --> 00:00:33.830 align:middle line:84%
>> I have understood for a
long time that change is part

00:00:33.830 --> 00:00:36.830 align:middle line:84%
of the essential nature of the
universe and that I've always

00:00:36.830 --> 00:00:39.640 align:middle line:90%
been afraid of change.

00:00:39.640 --> 00:00:42.820 align:middle line:84%
But today, I felt deeply
that change is a gift.

00:00:42.820 --> 00:00:45.480 align:middle line:90%


00:00:45.480 --> 00:00:47.820 align:middle line:84%
>> I wish I could
put it into words.

00:00:47.820 --> 00:00:53.880 align:middle line:10%
It was a sense of connectedness
that runs through all of us

00:00:53.880 --> 00:00:58.770 align:middle line:10%
and also a sense of the strength
of it and the power of it.

00:00:58.770 --> 00:01:01.155 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:01.155 --> 00:01:08.790 align:middle line:90%


00:01:08.790 --> 00:01:11.530 align:middle line:10%
>> Mystical experience has been
a part of human nature as far

00:01:11.530 --> 00:01:12.330 align:middle line:10%
as we know.

00:01:12.330 --> 00:01:15.300 align:middle line:84%
And most major religions
and religion traditions,

00:01:15.300 --> 00:01:19.260 align:middle line:84%
at the core, were about
a mystical experience.

00:01:19.260 --> 00:01:25.080 align:middle line:84%
Mysticism is unlike a belief
in something or knowledge

00:01:25.080 --> 00:01:26.520 align:middle line:90%
based on what someone tells you.

00:01:26.520 --> 00:01:29.460 align:middle line:10%
It's the direct
experience of that thing,

00:01:29.460 --> 00:01:32.610 align:middle line:10%
what's been called the ground of
being, to quote, Paul Tillich,

00:01:32.610 --> 00:01:37.300 align:middle line:10%
or all that is, [NON-ENGLISH]
in Hinduism, or in Christianity,

00:01:37.300 --> 00:01:38.630 align:middle line:90%
Christ-consciousness.

00:01:38.630 --> 00:01:40.720 align:middle line:84%
It's a direct
experience with all

00:01:40.720 --> 00:01:43.180 align:middle line:84%
that is with nature, with
God, as some would call it.

00:01:43.180 --> 00:01:52.950 align:middle line:90%


00:01:52.950 --> 00:01:55.860 align:middle line:84%
>> The word psychedelic
means "mind manifesting,"

00:01:55.860 --> 00:01:58.050 align:middle line:90%
and it came from a poem.

00:01:58.050 --> 00:02:01.140 align:middle line:10%
"To fathom hell
or sorrow angelic,

00:02:01.140 --> 00:02:03.320 align:middle line:10%
just take a pinch
of psychedelic."

00:02:03.320 --> 00:02:07.840 align:middle line:90%


00:02:07.840 --> 00:02:10.630 align:middle line:84%
>> The word psychedelic
was coined by a psychiatric

00:02:10.630 --> 00:02:14.410 align:middle line:84%
researcher named Humphry Osmond
in a letter to author Aldous

00:02:14.410 --> 00:02:19.300 align:middle line:84%
Huxley in 1956, before
Timothy Leary, Ken Kesey,

00:02:19.300 --> 00:02:20.890 align:middle line:90%
or the hippie movement.

00:02:20.890 --> 00:02:23.650 align:middle line:10%
And yet the use of
psychedelics goes back long

00:02:23.650 --> 00:02:25.840 align:middle line:10%
before the 20th century.

00:02:25.840 --> 00:02:28.300 align:middle line:84%
For as long as humans have
been roaming the Earth,

00:02:28.300 --> 00:02:31.075 align:middle line:84%
they've ingested and worshipped
these mysterious plants.

00:02:31.075 --> 00:02:40.270 align:middle line:90%


00:02:40.270 --> 00:02:42.720 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:42.720 --> 00:02:46.670 align:middle line:90%


00:02:46.670 --> 00:02:49.010 align:middle line:84%
>> In the 16th and
17th centuries,

00:02:49.010 --> 00:02:51.710 align:middle line:84%
when the Spanish conquistadors
arrived in the New World,

00:02:51.710 --> 00:02:55.100 align:middle line:84%
they were horrified
by what they observed.

00:02:55.100 --> 00:02:58.610 align:middle line:10%
They saw the native people
using a vast pharmacopeia

00:02:58.610 --> 00:03:03.020 align:middle line:10%
of native plants for purposes
of healing and divination.

00:03:03.020 --> 00:03:05.960 align:middle line:84%
And this was
entirely in conflict

00:03:05.960 --> 00:03:08.810 align:middle line:84%
with the orthodox,
rigid belief system

00:03:08.810 --> 00:03:11.510 align:middle line:84%
that conquistadors
brought with them.

00:03:11.510 --> 00:03:14.240 align:middle line:84%
>> The mushroom ceremonies
happened at night.

00:03:14.240 --> 00:03:18.140 align:middle line:84%
They involved invoking
spirits, divining the future,

00:03:18.140 --> 00:03:19.730 align:middle line:90%
looking for lost things.

00:03:19.730 --> 00:03:22.275 align:middle line:10%
And there were women who were
doing the ceremonies as well

00:03:22.275 --> 00:03:23.075 align:middle line:10%
as men.

00:03:23.075 --> 00:03:25.760 align:middle line:10%
So so many things,
probably, about that culture

00:03:25.760 --> 00:03:27.410 align:middle line:10%
was shocking.

00:03:27.410 --> 00:03:30.020 align:middle line:84%
And certainly, in
Christianity, the power

00:03:30.020 --> 00:03:34.250 align:middle line:84%
is given to priests who
speak on behalf of God.

00:03:34.250 --> 00:03:36.595 align:middle line:84%
And so the thing that is
scary about psychedelics

00:03:36.595 --> 00:03:38.345 align:middle line:84%
is that it gives power
directly to people.

00:03:38.345 --> 00:03:40.970 align:middle line:90%


00:03:40.970 --> 00:03:43.940 align:middle line:84%
>> The inquisition,
in the year 1616,

00:03:43.940 --> 00:03:47.360 align:middle line:84%
formally condemned the use
of hallucinogenic plants

00:03:47.360 --> 00:03:50.870 align:middle line:84%
and stated that the punishment
for anyone who would use such

00:03:50.870 --> 00:03:55.130 align:middle line:84%
plants, whether they be
natives or immigrant Spaniards,

00:03:55.130 --> 00:03:58.430 align:middle line:84%
was death by the cruelest
methods available.

00:03:58.430 --> 00:04:01.990 align:middle line:90%


00:04:01.990 --> 00:04:02.950 align:middle line:10%
>> 1938.

00:04:02.950 --> 00:04:04.885 align:middle line:90%
[ENGINES WHINING]

00:04:04.885 --> 00:04:10.230 align:middle line:90%


00:04:10.230 --> 00:04:14.100 align:middle line:10%
>> In 1938, as Europe stood
on the brink of world war,

00:04:14.100 --> 00:04:16.500 align:middle line:10%
a chemist working for a
pharmaceutical company

00:04:16.500 --> 00:04:19.709 align:middle line:10%
in Switzerland made a
most unusual discovery,

00:04:19.709 --> 00:04:23.640 align:middle line:10%
one that would alter the
course of human events to come.

00:04:23.640 --> 00:04:25.650 align:middle line:10%
>> Albert Hofmann was,
from a young person,

00:04:25.650 --> 00:04:29.790 align:middle line:10%
very focused on nature, kind
of a nature mystic almost.

00:04:29.790 --> 00:04:32.640 align:middle line:84%
And he worked at Sandoz
Pharmaceutical Companies.

00:04:32.640 --> 00:04:36.540 align:middle line:84%
And they were looking-- in
1938 is when he invented LSD.

00:04:36.540 --> 00:04:39.210 align:middle line:10%
It was also from ergot,
which is a fungus that

00:04:39.210 --> 00:04:40.860 align:middle line:10%
grows on wheat and barley.

00:04:40.860 --> 00:04:42.960 align:middle line:10%
He was looking at
various compounds

00:04:42.960 --> 00:04:45.300 align:middle line:10%
where he could start
with what was in ergot

00:04:45.300 --> 00:04:47.010 align:middle line:10%
and manipulate them
in different ways.

00:04:47.010 --> 00:04:50.160 align:middle line:84%
And LSD-25 was the
25th variation.

00:04:50.160 --> 00:04:52.710 align:middle line:84%
And in 1943, five
years later, he

00:04:52.710 --> 00:04:55.980 align:middle line:84%
had what he called a peculiar
presentiment that there was

00:04:55.980 --> 00:05:00.870 align:middle line:90%
something worthwhile in LSD-25.

00:05:00.870 --> 00:05:02.640 align:middle line:10%
>> He accidentally
ingested some,

00:05:02.640 --> 00:05:07.660 align:middle line:10%
because you don't need that much
LSD to get into your system.

00:05:07.660 --> 00:05:13.110 align:middle line:10%
And he had a really
unexpected experience.

00:05:13.110 --> 00:05:16.050 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't anything
that blew his mind,

00:05:16.050 --> 00:05:18.090 align:middle line:84%
but it was enough that
he paid attention.

00:05:18.090 --> 00:05:19.420 align:middle line:90%
>> It was on a Friday.

00:05:19.420 --> 00:05:22.140 align:middle line:84%
And so he went home
over the weekend.

00:05:22.140 --> 00:05:25.410 align:middle line:84%
And on Monday,
April 19, 1943, he

00:05:25.410 --> 00:05:28.110 align:middle line:84%
decided that he would
do a planned experiment,

00:05:28.110 --> 00:05:30.540 align:middle line:84%
and he would take
an amount that he

00:05:30.540 --> 00:05:33.480 align:middle line:84%
said was so small that he
thought nothing would happen.

00:05:33.480 --> 00:05:35.280 align:middle line:84%
But he wanted to
be extra cautious.

00:05:35.280 --> 00:05:38.190 align:middle line:84%
And that turned out
to be 250 micrograms,

00:05:38.190 --> 00:05:40.270 align:middle line:90%
250 millionths of a gram.

00:05:40.270 --> 00:05:42.900 align:middle line:10%
>> Which 100 micrograms is
usually enough for someone

00:05:42.900 --> 00:05:49.105 align:middle line:10%
who's naive to LSD to have
a full-blown experience.

00:05:49.105 --> 00:05:52.800 align:middle line:10%
>> Some of the symptoms
occurred immediately,

00:05:52.800 --> 00:05:57.270 align:middle line:10%
and very soon to become very,
very strong, very intense.

00:05:57.270 --> 00:06:04.320 align:middle line:10%
And I became anxious, and I
asked my laboratory assistant

00:06:04.320 --> 00:06:07.030 align:middle line:10%
to accompany me home.

00:06:07.030 --> 00:06:13.490 align:middle line:10%
And then, we went home by
bicycle because it was wartime,

00:06:13.490 --> 00:06:16.140 align:middle line:10%
and of course, I had no car.

00:06:16.140 --> 00:06:19.560 align:middle line:10%
And I reported about
this bicycle ride

00:06:19.560 --> 00:06:25.290 align:middle line:10%
because I had the feeling
that time would stand still.

00:06:25.290 --> 00:06:27.170 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:06:27.170 --> 00:06:32.820 align:middle line:90%


00:06:32.820 --> 00:06:35.650 align:middle line:10%
>> It's quite an
extraordinary property of LSD,

00:06:35.650 --> 00:06:39.520 align:middle line:10%
and yet that's a very,
very deep meaning.

00:06:39.520 --> 00:06:42.460 align:middle line:10%
If you have such a deep
affect of your whole body,

00:06:42.460 --> 00:06:45.370 align:middle line:10%
of your consciousness,
of your senses,

00:06:45.370 --> 00:06:50.895 align:middle line:10%
LSD must attack the very center
of our psychic existence.

00:06:50.895 --> 00:06:55.450 align:middle line:90%


00:06:55.450 --> 00:06:59.240 align:middle line:84%
>> Hofmann feared that his
nightmare would never end,

00:06:59.240 --> 00:07:01.760 align:middle line:84%
that he had permanently
damaged his mind,

00:07:01.760 --> 00:07:04.490 align:middle line:84%
and wondered what his wife and
children would think when they

00:07:04.490 --> 00:07:08.450 align:middle line:84%
returned home to find a
madman in the living room.

00:07:08.450 --> 00:07:10.460 align:middle line:90%
Slowly, the effects wore off.

00:07:10.460 --> 00:07:13.220 align:middle line:84%
And after a night's rest,
he entered his garden,

00:07:13.220 --> 00:07:16.310 align:middle line:84%
where everything was
teeming with life.

00:07:16.310 --> 00:07:19.970 align:middle line:84%
>> Woke up the next day and
felt refreshed, rejuvenated.

00:07:19.970 --> 00:07:21.980 align:middle line:84%
He found things to be
novel and interesting.

00:07:21.980 --> 00:07:24.980 align:middle line:10%
He went back to the lab to
figure out what had happened.

00:07:24.980 --> 00:07:28.580 align:middle line:84%
Nobody had thought that anything
in terms of the microgram range

00:07:28.580 --> 00:07:30.420 align:middle line:90%
could create an effect.

00:07:30.420 --> 00:07:33.170 align:middle line:84%
But in fact, he discovered
this very potent compound.

00:07:33.170 --> 00:07:36.290 align:middle line:84%
And then, Sandoz Pharmaceuticals
tested it in animals

00:07:36.290 --> 00:07:38.248 align:middle line:84%
for safety and
toxicity, then tested it

00:07:38.248 --> 00:07:40.290 align:middle line:84%
in some of the members of
Sandoz Pharmaceuticals.

00:07:40.290 --> 00:07:44.810 align:middle line:10%
>> But in 1943, Hofmann became
temporarily psychotic through

00:07:44.810 --> 00:07:47.120 align:middle line:10%
accidental ingestion
of the drug.

00:07:47.120 --> 00:07:49.490 align:middle line:84%
The door swung wide
open for research

00:07:49.490 --> 00:07:52.160 align:middle line:84%
into the nature of the
schizophrenic process,

00:07:52.160 --> 00:07:56.060 align:middle line:84%
and in a larger sense, into
the biochemistry of psychosis.

00:07:56.060 --> 00:08:01.730 align:middle line:10%
>> They believed that it might
be a tool to help psychiatrists

00:08:01.730 --> 00:08:05.510 align:middle line:10%
understand the inner
experience of their psychotic

00:08:05.510 --> 00:08:07.010 align:middle line:10%
or schizophrenic patients.

00:08:07.010 --> 00:08:11.210 align:middle line:84%
So they packaged samples
of LSD and shipped them out

00:08:11.210 --> 00:08:14.940 align:middle line:84%
to the leading psychiatric
researchers around the world.

00:08:14.940 --> 00:08:19.130 align:middle line:84%
>> I'm going to give you this
cup that contains lysergic

00:08:19.130 --> 00:08:21.770 align:middle line:90%
acid, 100 microgram.

00:08:21.770 --> 00:08:25.040 align:middle line:84%
>> --suggesting that they
try this compound themselves,

00:08:25.040 --> 00:08:27.950 align:middle line:84%
that it was a
psychotomimetic drug,

00:08:27.950 --> 00:08:31.700 align:middle line:84%
that it would induce the kind
of psychotic experience that

00:08:31.700 --> 00:08:35.690 align:middle line:84%
their patients were going
through and would better help

00:08:35.690 --> 00:08:39.260 align:middle line:84%
them understand and so
better help them treat.

00:08:39.260 --> 00:08:40.429 align:middle line:90%
>> How you feel?

00:08:40.429 --> 00:08:43.130 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, I feel very fine.

00:08:43.130 --> 00:08:45.620 align:middle line:84%
I feel very buoyant and
light and resilient.

00:08:45.620 --> 00:08:49.380 align:middle line:84%
I feel as though this
chair is not solid.

00:08:49.380 --> 00:08:50.660 align:middle line:90%
It seems to be--

00:08:50.660 --> 00:08:55.610 align:middle line:84%
I have a feeling
that my hands are not

00:08:55.610 --> 00:08:58.260 align:middle line:90%
